  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria

          -  Neonates were included if they had to undergo a venipuncture as part of routine
             medical care.

        Exclusion criteria

          -  Unstable neonates with respiratory support as well as neonates with a proven
             neurological abnormality were excluded.

          -  Newborns who had been administered sedatives, analgesics or naloxone during the past
             48 hours were excluded along with premature infants younger than 32 weeks post
             menstrual age.
      </textblock>
